The Chronicle Chronicle Reporter SUSPECTED touts and illegal money changers popularly known as Osiphatheleni on Wednesday attacked two police vehicles along Fort Street between 6th and 5th Avenue in the Bulawayo City Centre. <img class="alignnone wp-image-551059 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/Ford-Fiesta-1.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/Ford-Fiesta-1.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/Ford-Fiesta-1-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" />   Five police officers who were among occupants in the Ford Fiesta vehicles were injured during the attack and have since been taken to hospital. <img class="alignnone wp-image-551063 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/burnt-kombi-2.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/burnt-kombi-2.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/burnt-kombi-2-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Police had to call in reinforcements to disperse the marauding crowd just before they set the police vehicles alight. During the melee, two kombis were burnt to shells. <img class="alignnone wp-image-551065 size-full" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/burnt-kombi-1.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/burnt-kombi-1.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2021/06/burnt-kombi-1-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> It is not yet known who burnt kombis. More to followâ€¦